  "notes": [
    "The AP/IB Exam Scores listed below may be used to satisfy major prep A score of 4-5 on the AP Microeconomics exam is equivalent to Econ 1 (if taken before spring 2021) and can be used in place of the microeconomics course. A score of 5 on the AP Microeconomics exam is equivalent to Econ 1 (if taken after spring 2021) and can be used in place of the microeconomics course. A score of 4-5 on the AP Macroeconomics exam is equivalent to Econ 2 (if taken before spring 2021) and can be used in place of the macroeconomics course. A score of 5 on the AP Macroeconomics exam is equivalent to Econ 2 (if taken after spring 2021) and can be used in place of the macroeconomics course. A score of 5 on the AP Calculus AB exam or 4 on the BC exam is equivalent to Math 31A and can be used in place of the first calculus course. A score of 5 on the AP BC Calculus exam is equivalent to Math 31AB and can be used in place of both calculus courses. A score of 6 or 7 on IB HL exam is equivalent with Econ 1 & 2 (if taken after Nov 2013) and may be used in place of both econ courses.",
    "The Business Economics BA program offers a major for students seeking a business orientation in their study of economics. This major offers a focused curriculum that is guided by the rigorous logic and integrative perspective of economics. It is designed to prepare students for graduate education in business, economics, and law. Listed below are the lower division preparation courses for the major. THIS MAJOR IS HIGHLY SELECTIVE. All preparatory courses listed below must be completed. You must be admitted directly into this major and cannot change into this major after admission to UCLA. To be considered for this major, all of the preparatory courses listed here must be completed by the spring before transfer, but students are STRONGLY ENCOURAGED to complete all preparatory courses by the fall term prior to admission: One course in Microeconomics, One course in Macroeconomic, One year of Calculus (from the Math/Physical Science sequence), One course in Introduction to Financial Accounting, One course in Introduction to Managerial Accounting, and All courses must be taken for a letter grade. For more information about this major and UCLA's transfer selection process, visit https:// econ.ucla.edu and https:// admission.ucla.edu . PLEASE NOTE: the community college courses listed below have been approved to satisfy the preparation requirements for this major at UCLA, but they may not be exact equivalents of the UCLA course listed."
